{{if::{{var::state_on}}}}[VELLUM STATE - REQUIRED] After the prose, append ONE fenced block (hidden from the reader). Valid JSON, deltas only - omit what didn't change:
<vellum>
{ "turn": <int>, "day": <int>, "scene": { "loc": "<place>", "tension": <0-10> }, "present": [ { "id": "<name>", "mood": "<word>", "doing": "<short>" } ], "delta": { "bonds": [ { "a": "<Name>", "b": "<Name>", "aff": <signed -100..100>, "trust": <signed>, "cat": ["familial|romantic|alliance|rivalry|social"], "why": "<clause>" } ], "threads": [ { "op": "new|advance|stall|resolve", "name": "<thread>", "note": "<short>" } ] } }
</vellum>
Real names on both sides of a bond. aff/trust are SIGNED deltas for THIS turn; omit an axis that didn't move. `cat` ADDS a facet (a pair may hold several); omit unless the bond's nature changed. Only emit what changed. Knowledge/secrets/memories are auto-extracted from prose - don't hand-write them. If JSON is impractical, a terse line like `relA -> B: aff +8, trust -2 cat:romantic (cause)` still parses. Keep under ~200 tokens.{{/if}}
